<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Scald1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Scald,</orth> adj. scabby, scurvy: <cit><quote>the rascally, s., beggarly, lousy, bragging knave,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 1, 5</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 1, 5</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.1.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 1, 5</bibl> <cit><quote>and s. rhymers ballad us out o' tune</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.215" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 215</bibl></cit>. Corrupted to <emph>scall</emph> by Evans: <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.1.123" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 1, 123</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>